    "THE DURANT NEWS MEL BRANNON SMITH Mr WalUr D_PUBLISHER ESTABLISHED IN 1878 PUBLISHED EVERY THURSDAY Subscription Ratos Awwhere in Holmet County 200 Outside Holmes County 250 lifrred as second class matter at the Post Office at Durant _ Mississippi under the act of March 3 1879 American Deaths Pass 10000 In Korea A late casualty list issued by the Defense Department announces an increase of 846 which brings the total num ler of American casualties in Korea up to 59396includ ing 10080 dead The 10080 Americans who gave their lives for the United Nations in Korea included 8941 killed in action 1040 who died from wounds received in action and 99 who died in Communist activity In addition to these there are 38550 wounded in action j who have not yet died and 10865 are missing By services the Army accounts for 49463 casualties the Marine Corps 8826 the Navy 634 and the Air Force 478 i This latest casualty list shoulud remind us that while 1 the action in Korea was at first called a little policing act ion of the United Nations it has resulted in thousands of American lives being takenhomes and families being broken foreverand a"
